    "body": "## Problem\r\nEdit a file with a drive-letter path, then re-edit it without the drive letter and colon. This cause `path_fnamencmp` to loop infinitely as `len` never reaches 0, while `c1` and `c2` are already NUL.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nStill follow Vim and break the loop when either `c1` or `c2` is NUL.\r\nCommit 4bcee96 added parentheses for NUL check, ~but I haven't figured out what problem it was trying to solve.~\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-02T22:59:13Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40075#discussion_r3338117456"
                },
