                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/40075"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3338117456"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "In short, I think the condition in this PR is correct and easy to read.\n\nCommit [e18a578](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/e18a5783080f7c94f408ec5f53dedffdb69789e1#diff-ee99ba6760fdd541dc188393193e8a22af227a4df00a9d1e20f28e2062be845eR329) accidentally used `||` before `(p_fic`, commit [4bcee96](https://github.com/ntdiary/neovim/commit/4bcee963471abd939bb9edd1709418e30be7290f#diff-ee99ba6760fdd541dc188393193e8a22af227a4df00a9d1e20f28e2062be845eR329) fixed that, but also moved the `NUL` check into a grouped condition.\nThe bug remained hidden because there weren't any cases where strings had different lengths and `c1` and `c2` could both reach `NUL`. `c:/foo` vs `/foo` [happens to be](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/35373/changes/43bf045005b0fe819e85fdc44d7f7563f8ccda9d#diff-ee99ba6760fdd541dc188393193e8a22af227a4df00a9d1e20f28e2062be845eR384) such a case, which is why the infinite loop finally showed up.",
            "commit_id": "bb972e7aadcf145601b97106742cecafdffd2004",
            "created_at": "2026-06-02T01:41:25Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -414,9 +414,11 @@ int path_fnamencmp(const char *const fname1, const char *const fname2, size_t le\n   while (len > 0) {\n     c1 = utf_ptr2char(p1);\n     c2 = utf_ptr2char(p2);\n-    if ((c1 == NUL || c2 == NUL\n-         || (!((c1 == '/' || c1 == '\\\\') && (c2 == '\\\\' || c2 == '/'))))\n-        && (p_fic ? (c1 != c2 && utf_fold(c1) != utf_fold(c2)) : c1 != c2)) {\n+    if (c1 == NUL\n+        || c2 == NUL\n+        || (c1 != c2\n+            && ((c1 != '/' && c1 != '\\\\') || (c2 != '/' && c2 != '\\\\'))\n+            && (!p_fic || utf_fold(c1) != utf_fold(c2)))) {",
